HOUSE BILL 226
O3, G2 6lr0054
(PRE–FILED) CF SB 22
By: Chair, Appropriations Committee (By Request – Departmental – Disabilities)
Requested: September 25, 2025
Introduced and read first time: January 14, 2026
Assigned to: Appropriations
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted with floor amendments
Read second time: February 12, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Department of Disabilities – Housing Programs and Affiliated Foundations –
3 Establishment
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Department of Disabilities to establish affordable and
5 accessible housing programs; authorizing the Department to establish affiliated
6 foundations to work with certain programs and units of the Department to solicit
7 and accept funds, partner with individuals and entities, and promote certain
8 activities that support certain projects; prohibiting an affiliated foundation from
9 influencing certain determinations made by the Department; and generally relating
10 to the establishment of housing programs and affiliated foundations by the
11 Department of Disabilities.
12 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
13 Article – Human Services
14 Section 7–114(b)
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
17 BY adding to
18 Article – Human Services
19 Section 7–117
20 Annotated Code of Maryland
21 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0226*

2 HOUSE BILL 226
1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
3 Article – Human Services
4 7–114.
5 (b) The Department shall oversee and administer the following programs and
6 units:
7 (1) constituent services and ombudsmen programs;
8 (2) the Assistive Technology Guaranteed Loan Program under Subtitle 6
9 of this title;
10 (3) the Office of Personal Assistance Services, including the Attendant
11 Care Program under Subtitle 4 of this title;
12 (4) Telecommunications Access of Maryland under Subtitle 8 of this title;
13 (5) Telecommunications Devices and Distribution of Accessible
14 Information for Disabled Individuals under Subtitle 9 of this title;
15 (6) the Office of Disability Employment Advancement and Policy; [and]
16 (7) the Maryland Assistive Technology Program under Subtitle 14 of this
17 title; AND
18 (8) AFFORDABLE AND ACCESSIBLE HOUSING PROGRAMS.
19 7–117.
20 (A) IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 7–114 OF THIS SUBTITLE, THE DEPARTMENT
21 MAY ESTABLISH ONE OR MORE AFFILIATED FOUNDATIONS TO WORK WITH THE
22 MARYLAND ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY PROGRAM, THE ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY
23 GUARANTEED LOAN PROGRAM, THE OFFICE OF DISABILITY EMPLOYMENT
24 ADVANCEMENT AND POLICY, AND THE DEPARTMENT’S AFFORDABLE AND
25 ACCESSIBLE HOUSING PROGRAMS.
26 (B) THE PURPOSE OF AN AFFILIATED FOUNDATION IS TO:
27 (1) SOLICIT AND ACCEPT FUNDS AND PARTNER WITH INDIVIDUALS,
28 CORPORATIONS, AND OTHER ENTITIES TO SUPPORT INNOVATIVE PROJECTS
29 DESIGNED TO MAINTAIN, EXPAND, AND ENHANCE THE PROGRAMS AND UNITS
30 SPECIFIED IN SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION; AND

HOUSE BILL 226 3
1 (2) PROMOTE ACTIVITIES THAT:
2 (I) ENHANCE AWARENESS OF, ACCESS TO, AND EFFECTIVE USE
3 OF ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY, ACCESSIBLE INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, AND
4 ENVIRONMENTAL ADAPTATIONS THAT ALLOW INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES TO
5 PARTICIPATE IN EMPLOYMENT, EDUCATION, HOUSING, TRANSPORTATION, PUBLIC
6 SAFETY, RECREATION, HEALTH CARE, AND OTHER ASPECTS OF DAILY LIFE;
7 (II) SUPPORT TRAINING, TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE, AND
8 REASONABLE ACCOMMODATIONS THAT PROMOTE THE HIRING AND RETENTION OF
9 INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES IN PRIVATE AND PUBLIC SECTOR EMPLOYMENT;
10 AND
11 (III) CREATE OPPORTUNITIES FOR INTEGRATED, AFFORDABLE,
12 AND ACCESSIBLE HOUSING FOR INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES TO LIVE IN THE
13 COMMUNITIES OF THEIR CHOICE.
14 (C) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
15 (I) DEVELOP POLICIES FOR OPERATING EACH AFFILIATED
16 FOUNDATION THAT THE DEPARTMENT ESTABLISHES, INCLUDING THE AFFILIATED
17 FOUNDATION NAME; AND
18 (II) SUBMIT EACH POLICY DEVELOPED TO THE OFFICE OF THE
19 ATTORNEY GENERAL AND THE STATE ETHICS COMMISSION FOR REVIEW AND, IF
20 APPROPRIATE, APPROVAL IN ACCORDANCE WITH PARAGRAPHS (2) AND (3) OF THIS
21 SUBSECTION.
22 (2) THE OFFICE OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL SHALL:
23 (I) REVIEW THE POLICIES THE DEPARTMENT DEVELOPS
24 UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION FOR FORM AND LEGAL SUFFICIENCY;
25 AND
26 (II) IF APPROPRIATE, APPROVE THE POLICIES FOR USE IN
27 GOVERNING THE DEPARTMENT’S RELATIONSHIP WITH THE AFFILIATED
28 FOUNDATION.
29 (3) THE STATE ETHICS COMMISSION SHALL:

4 HOUSE BILL 226
1 (I) REVIEW THE POLICIES THE DEPARTMENT DEVELOPS
2 UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION THAT PERTAIN TO CONFLICTS OF
3 INTEREST; AND
4 (II) IF APPROPRIATE, APPROVE THE POLICIES FOR USE IN
5 GOVERNING AN OFFICIAL OR EMPLOYEE OF THE DEPARTMENT WHO ALSO SERVES
6 AS A DIRECTOR OR AN OFFICIAL OF THE AFFILIATED FOUNDATION.
7 (D) (1) AN AFFILIATED FOUNDATION MAY SOLICIT AND RECEIVE
8 CONTRIBUTIONS FROM BUSINESSES, GOVERNMENTAL ENTITIES, NONPROFIT
9 ORGANIZATIONS, AND INDIVIDUALS INTERESTED IN THE PROMOTION OF PROGRAMS
10 AND UNITS ADMINISTERED OR SUPPORTED BY THE DEPARTMENT.
11 (2) IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 7–113 OF THIS SUBTITLE AUTHORIZING
12 THE SECRETARY TO RECEIVE FUNDS FROM ANY PUBLIC OR PRIVATE SOURCE TO
13 CARRY OUT THE POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE DEPARTMENT, THE SECRETARY
14 SHALL RECEIVE AND DEPOSIT FUNDS FROM AN AFFILIATED FOUNDATION INTO A
15 SEPARATE SPECIAL FUND.
16 (E) (1) AN AFFILIATED FOUNDATION ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS
17 SECTION MAY NOT:
18 (I) BE CONSIDERED AN AGENCY OR INSTRUMENTALITY OF THE
19 STATE OR A UNIT OF THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH FOR ANY PURPOSE;
20 (II) MAKE, INFLUENCE, OR PARTICIPATE IN DETERMINATIONS
21 REGARDING ELIGIBILITY FOR ANY PROGRAM, BENEFIT, OR SERVICES
22 ADMINISTERED OR SUPPORTED BY THE DEPARTMENT; OR
23 (III) ESTABLISH, INFLUENCE, OR IMPLEMENT PUBLIC POLICY,
24 PROGRAM STANDARDS, PRIORITIES, OR ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA FOR THE
25 DEPARTMENT.
26 (2) A FINANCIAL OBLIGATION OR LIABILITY OF AN AFFILIATED
27 FOUNDATION ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSIDERED A DEBT
28 OR AN OBLIGATION OF THE STATE OR THE DEPARTMENT.
29 (F) (1) NOTWITHSTANDING §§ 5–501 THROUGH 5–504 OF THE GENERAL
30 PROVISIONS ARTICLE, AN OFFICIAL OR EMPLOYEE OF THE DEPARTMENT MAY
31 BECOME A DIRECTOR OR AN OFFICIAL OF AN AFFILIATED FOUNDATION
32 ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS SECTION.

HOUSE BILL 226 5
1 (2) AN OFFICIAL OR EMPLOYEE OF THE DEPARTMENT WHO SERVES
2 AS A DIRECTOR OR AN OFFICIAL OF AN AFFILIATED FOUNDATION ESTABLISHED
3 UNDER THIS SECTION:
4 (I) MAY NOT BE COMPENSATED, DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, BY
5 THE AFFILIATED FOUNDATION; AND
6 (II) MAY BE REIMBURSED FOR BONA FIDE EXPENSES INCURRED
7 IN THE PERFORMANCE OF ACTIVITIES UNDERTAKEN ON BEHALF OF THE
8 AFFILIATED FOUNDATION AS AUTHORIZED BY THE DEPARTMENT AND THE BOARD
9 OF DIRECTORS OF THE AFFILIATED FOUNDATION.
10 (3) (I) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL NOTIFY THE STATE ETHICS
11 COMMISSION IN WRITING WHENEVER THE DEPARTMENT ALLOWS AN OFFICIAL OR
12 EMPLOYEE OF THE DEPARTMENT TO SERVE AS A DIRECTOR OR AN OFFICIAL OF AN
13 AFFILIATED FOUNDATION.
14 (II) WITHIN 30 DAYS AFTER RECEIPT OF THE NOTICE UNDER
15 SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE STATE ETHICS COMMISSION SHALL
16 NOTIFY THE DEPARTMENT OF ANY OBJECTIONS OR CONCERNS PERTAINING TO THE
17 JOINT SERVICE IDENTIFIED IN THE NOTICE.
18 (III) ON RECEIPT OF A NOTICE FROM THE STATE ETHICS
19 COMMISSION UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE DEPARTMENT
20 SHALL REEXAMINE THE JOINT SERVICE IDENTIFIED IN THE NOTICE.
21 (4) ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 1 EACH YEAR, THE DEPARTMENT
22 SHALL REPORT TO THE GOVERNOR, THE LEGISLATIVE POLICY COMMITTEE OF THE
23 GENERAL ASSEMBLY IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT
24 ARTICLE, AND THE STATE ETHICS COMMISSION ON:
25 (I) THE NAMES OF THE OFFICIALS AND EMPLOYEES SERVING
26 AS A DIRECTOR OR AN OFFICIAL OF AN AFFILIATED FOUNDATION; AND
27 (II) HOW THE POLICIES ADOPTED UNDER SUBSECTION (C) OF
28 THIS SECTION HAVE BEEN IMPLEMENTED IN THE PRECEDING CALENDAR YEAR.
29 (G) (1) EACH YEAR, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL HIRE AN INDEPENDENT
30 CERTIFIED PUBLIC ACCOUNTANT TO:
31 (I) AUDIT AN AFFILIATED FOUNDATION ESTABLISHED UNDER
32 THIS SECTION; AND

6 HOUSE BILL 226
1 (II) SUBMIT TO THE DEPARTMENT A REPORT ON THE AUDIT OF
2 THE AFFILIATED FOUNDATION.
3 (2) NOTWITHSTANDING SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION, IF AN
4 AFFILIATED FOUNDATION HAS NOT BEEN AUDITED WITHIN THE PAST YEAR:
5 (I) THE AFFILIATED FOUNDATION MAY NOT SOLICIT AND
6 RECEIVE CONTRIBUTIONS; AND
7 (II) THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT ACCEPT CONTRIBUTIONS
8 FROM THE AFFILIATED FOUNDATION.
9 (H) CONTRIBUTIONS ACCEPTED BY THE DEPARTMENT FROM AN
10 AFFILIATED FOUNDATION ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS SECTION ARE SUPPLEMENTAL
11 TO AND ARE NOT INTENDED TO TAKE THE PLACE OF FUNDING THAT OTHERWISE
12 WOULD BE APPROPRIATED IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL OR CAPITAL BUDGET BILL
13 FOR THE DEPARTMENT.
14 (I) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO LIMIT OR RESTRICT THE
15 AUTHORITY OF THE DEPARTMENT OR OTHER AUTHORIZED GOVERNMENTAL
16 ENTITIES TO DETERMINE ELIGIBILITY OR MAKE POLICY DECISIONS.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
18 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
